  "details": "Joomla Solidres 2.13.3 contains a reflected cross-site scripting vulnerability that allows unauthenticated attackers to inject malicious scripts by manipulating multiple GET parameters including show, reviews, type_id, distance, facilities, categories, prices, location, and Itemid. Attackers can craft malicious URLs containing JavaScript payloads in these parameters to steal session tokens, login credentials, or manipulate site content when victims visit the crafted links.",
